description._content: Catalog #: 09_01888 Title: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo Date: 5/10/1905 Additional Information: During a ceremony in the Pentagon Building, Washington D.C. 5 July 1957, Lt. Gen. Clarence S. Irvine, (left) Deputy Chief of Staff, Material, USAF, presenting the Legion of Merit to Major George R. Boring. Brigadier General Clarence Irvine enjoyed a long distinguished military career, mainly involving engineering. He served with the XXI Bomber Command (B-29's) during WWII and continued to serve throughout the 1950s and 1960s. Tags: Brigadier General Clarence S.
